entries.s_10: You know the deceased? Perhaps you could shed some light on what could have happened.
entries.s_11: I don't know if I can help, but I am more than willing to assist the Mos Eisley Police if possible.
entries.s_12: When did you last see, uh, Bera Jeza?
entries.s_14: It's been a while. Perhaps a week or so.
entries.s_16: I see. Well, Ms. Jeza seems to have met her fate an hour or more ago. Probably an organized crime related death.
entries.s_20: Your friend had a large sum of spice on her. If I was a betting man, I'd say she was involved in the manufacture.
entries.s_22: Don't you need a lab for that sort of thing?
entries.s_24: Once we are done here I'll be interviewing her employer at the Mos Eisley Biolab. I have a feeling they are doing a little bit of moon lighting there.
entries.s_26: Is that the lab to the south?
entries.s_28: I don't know exactly.  You shouldn't worry about police matters.  Now excuse me.
entries.s_30: There really isn't anything else you can do here. We'll let you know if we find anything new.
entries.s_32: Sorry citizen, I have a murder scene to attend to.
entries.s_4: Sorry citizen, I have to attend to this murder scene.
entries.s_9: Is that Bera Jeza?  Oh no!
